\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF97</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolAddTime</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF98</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolShowTime</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF99</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolSchedule</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF100</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolScheduleMeeting</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF101</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolMakeRecurring</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF102</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolCopyActions</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF103</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolCopyMinutes</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF104</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolExportMeeting</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF105</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolAddWorkPackage</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF106</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolDeleteWorkPackage</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF107</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolBulkUpdate</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF108</td>\r\n<td width="183">ItemToolInvoiceSplit</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Tools</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF109</td>\r\n<td width="183">CustomField</td>\r\n<td width="205"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF110</td>\r\n<td width="183">Comments</td>\r\n<td width="205"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF111</td>\r\n<td width="183">IsTemplate</td>\r\n<td width="205">Bool</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF112</td>\r\n<td width="183">RootItem</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Id</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF113</td>\r\n<td width="183">Child</td>\r\n<td width="205">Item Id</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF114</td>\r\n<td width="183">Item</td>\r\n<td width="205">Comma separated list of item id\'s</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="116">SF115</td>\r\n<td width="183">Assigned To Usergroups</td>\r\n<td width="205"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Standard fields and their IDs (SF)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'standard-fields-and-their-ids-sf', '', '', '2016-04-26 09:00:31', '2016-04-26 08:00:31', '', 0, 'http://www.tenforce.com/portal/?post_type=tutorials&#038;p=94', 0, 'tutorials', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2016-02-04 10:21:17', '2016-02-04 09:21:17', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Alerts are triggered on specific events on an item, multiple alerts can be sent. An alert is sent to the destination user: depending on the user\'s alert channels, he will receive a notification in the web application ora notification via email.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Alert</strong> <strong>types</strong></span></h3>\r\nThe alert types define the alerts that can be used in the application, in a list configuration. They can be found in the Settings of the application, under the \'<span class="ph-breadcrumb">Workspaces and their setup\' chapter: \'</span><span class="ph-breadcrumb">Alert Types\'.</span>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Predefined</strong> alert types</span></h4>\r\nThe TenForce application has several predefined alert types.Only these predefined alert types are automatically triggered during item or timesheet events. When the event is raised, the configured notifications are sent to the destination users.The details of a predefined alert type cant be adjusted. However, it is possible to adjust the notification messages per list configuration.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Comment created:</span></em>triggered when a comment on an item is created and users are selected to be notified.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Item assigned to changed:</span></em> triggered when the assigned-to of the item is changed.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Item changed:</span></em> triggered when a standard field is changed. A standard field is a field defined by TenForce.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Item created:</span></em> triggered when a new item is created.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Item due:</span></em> triggered when the due date of the item is reached.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Item status changed:</span></em> triggered when the status of the item is changed.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Timesheet due:</span></em> triggered when the due date of the timesheetis reached.</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Timesheet rejected:</span></em> triggered when the timesheet was rejected.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Custom</strong><strong></strong><strong>alert</strong> <strong>types</strong></span></h4>\r\n<b></b>A TenForce ScriptWriter and the workspace administrator are able to manage customalert types. Alert types can be created for the application. Customalert types allow each workspace configurator to define the notification message themself. With the alert type, the application splits the mail content from the automation layer.\r\n\r\nA workspace configurator is allowed to link alert types, defined by the workspace administrator, to its list configuration. Own defined alert types will not be raised on item events. Automations scripts, linked to the item, need to trigger these types of alerts.\r\n\r\nThe unique <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>code</b> </span>indentief the alert type. The <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>screenlabel</b> </span>is used in the list configuration screen while managing alerts.\r\n\r\nThe condition, written in the <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>active expression</b></span>, must be met to execute the alert. When creating a new alert type, we advice you not to define an active expression. The condition of an active expression is compared with system components of the application. The system components are not retrievable by the alert type creator or TenForce ScriptWriter.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>scope flag</b></span> defines for object type the alert is created. The scope can be:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Item: Alerts triggered on item events</li>\r\n	<li>Timesheet: Alerts triggered on timesheet events</li>\r\n	<li>General: Alerts triggered on another object.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>Is recurring</b></span> defines if an alert can be raised again after this current alert is raised. When the Is recurring flag is active, a duplicate alert is initialized when the current event is raised. When the event reoccurs, the alert is triggered again.\r\n\r\nThe workspace administrator needs to select an alert <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>formula</b></span>. In the alert formula, a condition is validated. When the conditionis valid, the alert is raised. The formula is a replacement of the active expression, TenForce ScriptWriters are able to created alert formulas.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>active</b> </span>flag defines if the alert type can be used, an inactive flag can be considered as a logical delete. Do not forget to activate this flag when creating a new alert type.\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Message</strong> <strong>templates</strong></span></h4>\r\nPer alert type, the workspace administrator is able to define a default message (=message template) for the notifications. These messages are copied to the alert when alerts are added to a list configuration.\r\n\r\nThe <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>message title</b></span> defines the subject of the mail that is sent to the destination user. The <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>message body</b></span> contains the mail message. TenForce allows you to provide a HTML text. The HTML text allows the configurator to foresee styling in the notification mail.\r\n\r\nWhen sending a notification mail, the <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>plain text </b></span>is also sent to the user. The plain text is shown in a mail client that doesnt support HTML. Often, mail clients do not support mail with HTML content. The plain text message solves this issue.\r\n\r\nWhen a notification is not sent via a mail, but shown on the web, a <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>tooltip message</b></span> is shown.\r\n\r\nIn the notification message, system parameters can be used using the curly brackets ({}). You can find a list of used parameter ids in the online help of the application (URL: &lt;tenforceurl&gt;/Pages/OnlineHelp/default/en/index.html?parameters_and_standard_fields.htm).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Manage</strong> <strong>alerts</strong> <strong>per</strong> <strong>list</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The \'alerts\' tab in the settings of a list lists all configured alerts for thatlist configuration.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">When a list is configured for the first time, TenForce automatically foresees 3 notification events: an alert is sent when an item and comment is created and when the item has reached the due date.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Alerts are added to each item created in the list. When the notification rules are adjusted, they will not have effect on already created item. The new notification rules will only have impact on newly created items in that list. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Managing notification, the </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>type</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of the notification event must be selected. The type of the notification defines on which item event the notification is sent.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>priority</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> defines the level of importance. Depending on the priority, the alert channel of the destination person is chosen. Each user can have a different alert channel per priority.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The notification must be sent to a user. The workspace configurator defines to which user, using the </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>destination type</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the notification is sent. When selection as destination type the value (specific person), a </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>destination person</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> must be selected. In this case, the same person will always receive a notification when a specific event is raised.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>active</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> flag defines if the alert can be triggered, an inactive flag can be considered as a logical delete. Do not forget to activate this flag when creating an alert for this list.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The workspace configurator is able to adjust </span><b><span style="text-decoration: underline;">parameters</span> </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">for some alert types. The parameters give the workspace configurator the ability to adjust the notification trigger. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">It is possible to adjust the notification </span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>template</b></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The subject, message and tooltip can be adjusted per notification. Click the </span><b>customize</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> action in the template column to adjust the notification message. Already created alerts are not changed. Only newly created alerts will use the update notification text provided in the template.</span>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Destination types</span></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">TenForce has provided a pre-configured list of destination types. In the lifetime of an item, the value of the destination type can change. The application has foreseen 4 groups to send notifications to: the c</span>reator, the owner (=\'AssignedTo\'), the originator or otherwise, dedicated users can be used.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Creator:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the user who has created the item</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Manager of the creator:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the manager of the creator of the item. The manager is defined on the organization unit of the creator.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Creator organization unit:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">all users defined in the organization unit of the creator of the item.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">\'Assigned to\'/\'Owner\':</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the current owner of the item, the owner is defined in the Assigned to field.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Manager of the owner:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the manager of the current owner of the item. The manager is defined on the organization unit of the owner.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Owner organization unit:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">all users defined in the organization unit of the current owner of the item.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Originator:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the user who has initiated the creation of the item. Often a manager ask his secretary to create tasks. In this case the creator is the secretary and the manager is the originator.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Manager of the source organization unit:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the manager of the user who has initiated the item (= originator). The manager is defined on the organization unit of the originator field.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Source organization unit:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">all users defined in the organization unit of the user who has initiated the item (= originator).</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Parent item owner:</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">the owner of the linked parent item, if one is defined.</span></li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">List owner</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span></em>the default owner for new items in the list. (?)</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Domain owner</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span></em>the system userof the application(?)</li>\r\n	<li><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">(Specific person):</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">a specific user, defined in the \'</span>destination person\'<span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> field.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>\'Destination\' organization unit:</em></span>all users defined in the organization unit of \'destination person\'.</li>\r\n	<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Manager of the \'destination\' organization unit:</em></span>the manager of the \'destination person\'. The manager is defined on the organization unit of the \'destination person\' field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Parameters</span></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For some alerttypes, additional parameters can be defined. The parameters give the workspace configurator the ability to adjust the notification trigger. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Item assigned to changed\r\n</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">The workspace configurator can define the </span><b>From Person Id </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the </span><b>To Person Id</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Only when the old assigned to and the adjusted assigned to matches the criteria, a notification is sent. The validation of the user is only checked when the parameter is defined. If the parameters arent set, then the notification when the owner changes always triggers.\r\n</span>In order to set the Person Id, you need to know the user identifier. To retrieve the user identifier, you need to open the item detail page of the user. In the address bar of the browser, you can find the id in the url. The number after the last / is the person id.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Item status changed\r\n</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">The workspace configurator can defined the </span><b>From Status Id </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the </span><b>To Status Id</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Only when the old assigned to and the adjusted assigned to matches the criteria, a notification is sent. The validation of the user is only checked when the parameter is defined. If the parameters arent set, then the notification when the owner changes always triggers.\r\n</span>In order to set the Status Id, you need to know the status identifier. It is only possible to retrieve the status identifier when you have the knowledge to debug HTML.\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Contact </span><a href="mailto:support@tenforce.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">support@tenforce.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to retrieve a list with all status identifiers in your application.</span></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Item due\r\n</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">A notification is sent when the due date is reached. The workspace configurator can define how many </span><b style="line-height: 1.6471;">days in advanced</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the alert should be raised.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Alert<strong></strong><strong>t</strong>emplates</span><b></b></h4>\r\nThe alert type message template iscopied when alerts are added to a list configuration.\r\nExisting alerts are not impacted when adjusting the notification message in the alert type. An adjusted notification message as only effect on newly created alerts in a list configuration.\r\nThe subject, message and tool tip can be adjusted per notification. Click the customize action in the template column to adjust the notification message.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Manage</strong> <strong>alerts</strong> <strong>via</strong> <strong>scripting</strong></span></h3>\r\nAlerts can be configured in the web application, but they can also be created ad-hoc in scripting.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Createan alert</strong></span></h4>\r\n(TODO)\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Raise an alert</strong></span></h4>\r\n(TO CHECK WITH SR. DEV)\r\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp">public static void RaiseAlert(Item item, List list, string template, List&lt;int&gt; users)\r\n {\r\n // No users\r\n if (users.Count == 0)\r\n return;\r\n\r\n // If not yet loaded\r\n if (list.AlertTemplates.Length == 0)\r\n {\r\n // Get alert templates for this list\r\n if (!Api.AlertTemplates.GetAlertTemplatesByList(list))\r\n throw new ScriptException("GetAlertTemplatesByList: " + Api.AlertTemplates.ErrorMessage);\r\n }\r\n\r\n // Find alert template\r\n var alertTemplate = list.AlertTemplates.FirstOrDefault(f =&gt; f.Active &amp;&amp; f.Name.Equals(template, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\r\n if (alertTemplate == null)\r\n return;\r\n\r\n // Send alerts\r\n users\r\n .Select(u =&gt; new Alert\r\n {\r\n Item = item,\r\n Destination = new AlertDestination { Id = 11 }, // Specific person\r\n Priority = alertTemplate.Priority, \r\n Status = new AlertStatus { Id = 2 }, // Initialized\r\n Template = alertTemplate,\r\n User = new User { Id = u },\r\n })\r\n .Where(a =&gt;\r\n {\r\n if (!Api.Alerts.Create(a))\r\n throw new ScriptException("Alert Failed: " + Api.AlertStatuses.ErrorMessage);\r\n\r\n return true;\r\n })\r\n .Select(a =&gt; new AlertUser { Alert = a, User = new User { Id = a.User.Id }, Show = true })\r\n .ForEach(a =&gt;\r\n {\r\n var userId = a.Alert.User.Id;\r\n\r\n // Create alertuser\r\n if (!Api.AlertUsers.Create(a))\r\n throw new ScriptException("AlertUser failed: " + Api.AlertUsers.ErrorMessage);\r\n\r\n // Lost this during save\r\n a.Alert.Destination = new AlertDestination { Id = 11 };\r\n a.Alert.User = new User { Id = userId };\r\n\r\n if (!Api.Alerts.Raise(a.Alert))\r\n throw new ScriptException("Raise failed: " + Api.Alerts.ErrorMessage);\r\n });\r\n }</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n', 'Alerts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'alerts', '', '', '2016-04-28 11:06:03', '2016-04-28 10:06:03', '', 0, 'http://www.tenforce.com/portal/?post_type=tutorials&#038;p=98', 0, 'tutorials', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2016-02-04 10:22:59', '2016-02-04 09:22:59', 'Next toparent-child relations, non-hierarchical relations between 2 items can alsobe created.An item relation gives the user the opportunity to have a many to many relation between items. Using item relation types, different types of relations can be managed.\r\n\r\nItem relation types should first be configured in the web application, then the custom fields should be added to the correct list, and then a user or a script can add a relation between items of the correct types.\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>1. Configurea new item relation type in the web application</strong></span></h4>\r\nGo to the settings of the application by using the link in the right hand corner. In the \'Workspace and their setup\' topic, choose\'Item Relation Types\' to configure them.\r\n<em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Remark:</span></em>In order to view existing and create new item relation types, view custom fields application privileges must be granted to you.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ItemRelationType.png" rel="attachment wp-att-326"><img class="alignnone wp-image-326 " src="http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/ItemRelationType.png" alt="ItemRelationType" width="656" height="184" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe \'Code\' defines the unique identifier of the item relation type. The \'Screen label\' is the label that is used in the list customization.\r\nWhen creating a new item relation type, 2 custom fields are created in the background.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The custom field that will represent the item relation from a \'from-item\' to another item (the \'to-item\') will be defined in the \'code1\' and \'referer\' values.</li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.6471;">The custom field that will represent the item relation from the \'to-item\' to the from-item will be defined in the \'code2\' and \'refers to\' values.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Remark:</span> </em>The \'code1\' and \'code2\' values must be unique between all standard fields and custom fields.The screen labels (\'referer\' and \'refers to\' values) are used in the item details screens, visible forthe user.\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>2. Addthe custom field(s) on the list(s) in the web application</strong></span></h4>\r\nGo to the \'customize\' page of the list(s) and create a new relation field: select the correct \'target list\' and \'item relation type\'.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/CField_IRs.png" rel="attachment wp-att-343"><img class="alignnone wp-image-343" src="http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/CField_IRs.png" alt="CField_IRs" width="634" height="293" /></a>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>3.a. Createan itemrelation of a certain type between itemsin the web application</strong></span></h4>\r\nNow arelation between 2 items can be created in the web application by a user whohas the privileges to do so.\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>3.b. Create an itemrelation of a certain type between items via scripting</strong></span></h4>\r\nAn item relation can also be created via scripting when the relation type and the 2 items are known.\r\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp">//TODO: Provide item and item relation type\r\nvar irTypeId  = ...;\r\nvar fromitemId  = ...;\r\nvar toItemId  = ...;\r\n\r\n// Get correct item relation\r\nvar itemRelation = new ItemRelation\r\n{\r\n    ItemRelationType = new ItemRelationType { Id = irTypeId },\r\n    FromItem = new Item { Id = fromitemId },\r\n    ToItem = new Item { Id = toItemId }\r\n};\r\nif (!Api.ItemRelations.Create(itemRelation))\r\n    throw new ScriptException("Unable to create the item relation: " + Api.ItemRelations.ErrorMessage);</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>4. Retrieveitem relationsvia scripting</strong></span></h4>\r\nTo get the item relations for a certain item of a given type:\r\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp">// TODO: Provide item and item relation type\r\nItem item = ...;\r\nint irTypeId = ...;\r\n\r\n// Get all item relations of the item\r\nif (!Api.ItemRelations.GetItemRelationsByItem(item))\r\n  throw new ScriptException(Api.ItemRelations.ErrorMessage);\r\n\r\n// Get allitemrelationsof the correct item relation type\r\nvar relations = item.ItemRelations.Where(i =&gt; i.ItemRelationTypeId == type);</pre>\r\n<span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal;"></span>\r\n<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>5. Deleteitem relations via scripting</strong></span></h4>\r\nTo deletea specificitem relation type between a from and to item:\r\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp">//TODO: Provideitemanditemrelationtype\r\nvar irTypeId  = ...;\r\nvar fromitemId  = ...;\r\nvar toItemId  = ...;\r\n\r\n// Get correct item relation\r\nvar itemRelation = new ItemRelation\r\n{\r\n    ItemRelationType = new ItemRelationType { Id = irTypeId },\r\n    FromItem = new Item { Id = fromitemId },\r\n    ToItem = new Item { Id = toItemId }\r\n};\r\nif (!Api.ItemRelations.Destroy(itemRelation))\r\n    throw new ScriptException("Unable to delete the item relation: " + Api.ItemRelations.ErrorMessage);</pre>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Item relations', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'item-relations', '', '', '2016-04-26 08:59:00', '2016-04-26 07:59:00', '', 0, 'http://www.tenforce.com/portal/?post_type=tutorials&#038;p=104', 0, 'tutorials', '', 0),
