(227, 6, '2016-03-30 14:26:16', '2016-03-30 13:26:16', 'When creating multiple scripts for the same list, it\'s very important to keep in mind the order in which they will be executed, as they can bemapped on different events.\nIf the scripts are mapped on the same event, a sequence can be added in the web application to determine the order.\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Creation\n</strong></span>On the creation of an item, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeValidation(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeValidationOnCreate(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterValidation(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterValidationOnCreate(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeSave(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeCreate(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterCreate(null, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterSave(null, NewItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Update</strong></span>\nWhen an existing item is updated, these events are triggered in this order.\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeValidation(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeValidationOnUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterValidation(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterValidationOnUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeStateTransition (Item, stateTransition), in case the state transition of the</li>\n	<li>BeforeSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterStateTransition (Item, stateTransition), in case the status changed</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Move\n</strong></span>When an item is moved to another list, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeMove(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterMove(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Copy\n</strong></span>When an item is copied, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeCopy (OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterCopy (OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Delete\n</strong></span>When an item is deleted, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeDelete(OldItem, null)</li>\n	<li>AfterDelete(OldItem, null)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Link child to parent\n</strong></span>When an item (child) is linked to another item (parent), these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeLinkChild (ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeLinkParent(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkParent(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkChild(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Unlink parent from child\n</strong></span>When an item (parent) is unlinked froma linkeditem (child), these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeUnlinkChild(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeUnlinkParent(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUnlinkParent(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUnlinkChild(ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Time registration\n</strong></span>When time is added on items (for time registration), these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeTimeRegistration (Item)</li>\n	<li>AfterTimeRegistration (Item)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Save schedule of items\n</strong></span>When items (predecessors and successors) are scheduled, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeLinkSuccessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeLinkPredecessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkPredecessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkSuccessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Deleteschedule of items\n</strong></span>When the schedule of items (predecessor or successor) is removed, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeUnlinkSuccessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeUnlinkPredecessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUnlinkPredecessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUnlinkSuccessor (PredecessorItem, SuccessorItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Meeting item - Attendees (create, update andremove)\n</strong></span>When attendees of a meeting are created, updated or removed, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n</ol>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Meeting item - Agenda Topics(save, remove)\n</strong></span>When agenda topicsof a meeting are savedor removed, these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterUpdate(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterSave(OldItem, NewItem)</li>\n</ol>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Meeting item - Link actionto agenda topic\n</strong></span>When an action is linked to an agenda topicsof a meeting , these events are triggered in this order:\n<ol>\n	<li>BeforeLinkChild (ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>BeforeLinkParent (ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkParent (ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n	<li>AfterLinkChild (ChildItem, ParentItem)</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;', 'Order of event triggering', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '138-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-30 14:26:16', '2016-03-30 13:26:16', '', 138, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/138-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(228, 6, '2016-02-15 12:11:08', '2016-02-15 11:11:08', 'Triggered after saving an item. This means that this event is triggered aftercreating and updating an item.\n<ul class="methods">\n	<li>AfterSave ( OldItem, NewItem );</li>\n</ul>\nThe arguments in this list consist of:\n<ul class="arguments">\n	<li>OldItem of type Item or Meeting: Item or Meeting in the state before the change. (null when creating a new item)</li>\n	<li>NewItem of type Item: Item in the state after the change.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nAn example using the AfterSave event:\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW " data-enlighter-language="csharp">using TenForce.Execution.AddIns.Constants;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2.Objects;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting.Api2;\n\nnamespace Tenforce.Execution.Addins.MyAddin\n{\n public class AfterSave : Script&lt;ScriptContext&gt;\n {\n private static IApi Api { get { return Factory.Instance; } }\n private IFieldRetriever FieldRetriever { get; set; }\n\n public AfterSave()\n {\n FieldRetriever = new FieldHandler.DefaultFieldRetriever();\n }\n\n [EntryPoint]\n public void RunCode()\n {\n var oldItem = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter("OldItem") as Item;\n var newItem = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter("NewItem") as Item;\n \n if (newItem == null) throw new ScriptException("NewItem is null");\n var newHandler = new FieldHandler(newItem, FieldRetriever);\n if (oldItem != null)\n {\n var oldHandler = new FieldHandler(oldItem, FieldRetriever);\n if (newHandler.AreEquals(C.Originator, oldHandler))\n return;\n }\n\n // Read originator\n var user = Api.Users.Read(handler.GetString(C.Originator));\n\n // Save "from" email address used for email communication\n var from = new ItemField\n {\n FieldId = handler.FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(C.Email.From),\n Item = handler.Item,\n Value = user.GetMailAddress().ToString()\n };\n\n // Save field on protected tab\n using (new Impersonate(Api, true))\n {\n if (!Api.ItemFields.Update(from, false))\n throw new ScriptException("Failed to update itemfield " + from.FieldId + " on item " + from.Item.Id + ": " + Api.ItemFields.ErrorMessage);\n }\n }\n }\n}</pre>', 'AfterSave', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-15 12:11:08', '2016-02-15 11:11:08', '', 78, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/78-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(229, 6, '2016-02-15 10:36:44', '2016-02-15 09:36:44', '<div id="ember636" class="ember-view markdown">\n\nTriggered before validation of the item fields during creating and updating an item, this validation includes the check to see that all mandatory fields are filled in.\nOne of the most common usages of the BeforeValidation event is setting the Title field while it is not available on the CNI. This way the user doesnt need to supply a title, were setting it via a script instead. You cant save the changes to the item in both the after and before event of this trigger because both events occur before the save method of pmOperation.\n<ul>\n	<li>BeforeValidation ( Item );</li>\n	<li>   OR</li>\n	<li>BeforeValidation ( OldItem, NewItem );</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\nThe arguments in this list consist of:\n<ul class="arguments">\n	<li>Item of type Item: Current item</li>\n	<li>   OR</li>\n	<li>OldItem of type Item: Current item</li>\n	<li>NewItem of type Item: Current item</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nAn example could be:\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp" data-enlighter-theme="classic">using System;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2.Objects;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting.Api2;\n\nnamespace Tenforce.Execution.Addins.MyAddin\n{\n public class HelloWorld : Script&lt;ScriptContext&gt;\n {\n private IApi Api { get { return Factory.Instance; } }\n private IFieldRetriever FieldRetriever { get; set; }\n\n public HelloWorld()\n {\n FieldRetriever = new FieldHandler.DefaultFieldRetriever();\n }\n\n [EntryPoint]\n public void RunCode()\n {\n var item = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter("Item") as Item;\n // Use FieldHandler to do operations on the Item object\n var handler = new FieldHandler(item, FieldRetriever);\n // Set the title field value\n handler.SetString("Title", "Title - " + DateTime.Now.ToLongDateString());\n\n AddFeedBack("Hello World");\n }\n }\n}</pre>\n&nbsp;', 'BeforeValidation', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '192-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-15 10:36:44', '2016-02-15 09:36:44', '', 192, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/192-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(231, 6, '2016-02-15 11:39:56', '2016-02-15 10:39:56', '<div id="ember636" class="ember-view markdown">\n\nTriggered after validation of the item fields during creating and updating an item, this validation includes the check to see that all mandatory fields are filled in.\n\n</div>\n<ul class="methods">\n	<li>AfterValidation( Item );</li>\n</ul>\nThe arguments in this list consist of:\n<ul class="arguments">\n	<li>OldItem of type Item: Item in the state before the change.</li>\n	<li>NewItem of type Item: Item in the state after the change.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;', 'AfterValidation', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '171-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-15 11:39:56', '2016-02-15 10:39:56', '', 171, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/171-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(232, 6, '2016-02-15 11:39:59', '2016-02-15 10:39:59', '<div id="ember636" class="ember-view markdown">\n\nThis event is the same as the AfterValidation event, except that it is only triggered when updating an item.\n\n</div>\n<ul class="methods">\n	<li>AfterValidationOnUpdate( OldItem, NewItem );</li>\n</ul>\nThe arguments in this list consist of:\n<ul class="arguments">\n	<li>OldItem of type Item: Item in the state before the change.</li>\n	<li>NewItem of type Item: Item in the state after the change.</li>\n</ul>', 'AfterValidationOnUpdate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '173-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-15 11:39:59', '2016-02-15 10:39:59', '', 173, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/173-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(233, 6, '2016-02-15 11:40:27', '2016-02-15 10:40:27', '<div id="ember636" class="ember-view markdown">\n\nThis event is the same as the BeforeValidation event, except that it is only triggered when creating a new item.\n\n</div>\n<ul class="methods">\n	<li>BeforeValidationOnCreate(Item);</li>\n</ul>\nThe arguments in this list consist of:\n<ul class="arguments">\n	<li>OldItem of type Item: Item in the state before the change.</li>\n	<li>NewItem of type Item: Item in the state after the change.</li>\n</ul>', 'BeforeValidationOnCreate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-15 11:40:27', '2016-02-15 10:40:27', '', 193, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/193-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
