(271, 6, '2016-02-16 16:00:55', '2016-02-16 15:00:55', 'Logging of messages can be done to log files, which can be found in the data home folder. Depending on the chosen level, the lines will be found in another file.\n\nThis is how logging can be added:\n<pre>LogManager.Instance.LogMessage(new StandardMessage(message, level));\n</pre>\n<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">Warning and error</span></strong>\n\nTo retrieve the log lines in the log file with name User_Web_ErrorWarning_RobinsonLog_&#91;DateTime&#93;.txt use these levels:\n<pre>//Error logging\nLogManager.Instance.LogMessage(new StandardMessage(message, LogLevel.Error));\n//Warning logging\nLogManager.Instance.LogMessage(new StandardMessage(message, LogLevel.Warning));</pre>\n<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">Infoanddebug</span></strong>\n\nTo retrieve the log lines in the log file with name User_Web_InfoDebug_RobinsonLog_&#91;DateTime&#93;.txt use these levels:\n<pre>//Info logging\nLogManager.Instance.LogMessage(new StandardMessage(message, LogLevel.Info));\n//Debug logging\nLogManager.Instance.LogMessage(new StandardMessage(message, LogLevel.Debug));</pre>', 'How to add logging in log files?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-add-logging-in-log-files', '', '', '2016-02-16 16:01:09', '2016-02-16 15:01:09', '', 269, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-add-logging-in-log-files/?show_answer=271#answer_271', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
