(310, 6, '2016-02-23 09:44:25', '2016-02-23 08:44:25', 'The optimal way to retrieve and update only 1 field of an item, is by reading that specific ItemField. It is much more efficient than loading a full item.\n\n<em><span style="text-decoration: underline">Remark</span></em>: We need to use the field ID, combined with SF or CF, not the code of the field!\n\nThis piece ofshows youhow a standard field (e.g. the title (=SF2)) of an item can be changed:\n<pre>//Item with ID 123\nvar itemId = 123;\n\n//Change the standard field with ID 2 (=&#039;Title&#039;)\nvar field = Api.ItemFields.Read(itemId, &quot;SF2&quot;);\nfield.Value = New field value;\nif (!Api.ItemFields.Update(field))\n  throw new ScriptException(&quot;An error occurred while updating the &#039;Title&#039; field&quot;);</pre>\nThis piece ofshows youhow a custom field (e.g. the longdescription (=CF45)) of an item can be changed:\n<pre>//ItemwithID123\nvaritemId=123;\n\n//ChangethecustomfieldwithID45(=&#039;Long description&#039;)\nvarfield=Api.ItemFields.Read(itemId,&quot;CF45&quot;);\nfield.Value=Newfieldvalue;\nif(!Api.ItemFields.Update(field))\nthrownewScriptException(&quot;Anerroroccurredwhileupdatingthe&#039;Long description&#039; field&quot;);</pre>', 'How to retrieve and update one field of an item?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-retrieve-and-update-one-field-of-an-item', '', '', '2016-02-23 09:45:33', '2016-02-23 08:45:33', '', 309, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-retrieve-and-update-one-field-of-an-item/?show_answer=310#answer_310', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
