(418, 25, '2016-04-07 10:17:00', '2016-04-07 09:17:00', 'Nice to know: Before version 2.220 the product code contained a "lock" when executing admin scripts. This means that when you execute a script while another one is running, this script will only start when the first one ends.', 'How to trigger an admin script via OData from within INCA?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-trigger-an-admin-script-via-odata-from-within-inca', '', '', '2016-04-07 10:17:00', '2016-04-07 09:17:00', '', 134, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-trigger-an-admin-script-via-odata-from-within-inca/?show_answer=418#answer_418', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(419, 25, '2016-04-07 10:33:15', '2016-04-07 09:33:15', 'In the example above, setting the Int, Number and Boolean value should be:\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetInt</span><span>(</span><span>int_field_code</span><span>,</span> <span>3</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetNumber</span><span>(</span><span>int_field_code</span><span>,3M</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetBool</span><span>(</span><span>bool_field_code</span><span>,</span> <span>true</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n\nsettingmultiple int :\nhandler.SetMultipleInts("mulpiple_field_code", new List&lt;int&gt;() { 1, 2, 3 });\nhandler.SetMultipleIntsByCodes("mulpiple_field_code", new List&lt;int&gt;() { "lov_code_1", "lov_code_2", "lov_code_3" });', 'How to retrieve and update multiple fields of an item?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item-2', '', '', '2016-04-07 10:33:15', '2016-04-07 09:33:15', '', 318, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item/?show_answer=419#answer_419', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(420, 25, '2016-04-07 13:09:32', '2016-04-07 12:09:32', 'that needs to behandler.SetMultipleIntsByCodes(mulpiple_field_code, new List&lt;string&gt;() { lov_code_1, lov_code_2, lov_code_3 });', 'How to retrieve and update multiple fields of an item?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item-3', '', '', '2016-04-07 13:09:32', '2016-04-07 12:09:32', '', 318, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item/?show_answer=420#answer_420', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(421, 37, '2016-04-07 13:52:11', '2016-04-07 12:52:11', 'Much faster would be to do this:\n<pre>var handler = new FieldHandler(item, FieldRetriever); \nvar selected = handler.GetLov(field_code); \nif (selected != null &amp;&amp; selected.Code.Equals(value_code, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)) \n{ \n// Do something \n}</pre>', 'How to work with ComboBox custom fields?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-work-with-combobox-custom-fields-2', '', '', '2016-04-07 13:52:35', '2016-04-07 12:52:35', '', 253, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-work-with-combobox-custom-fields/?show_answer=421#answer_421', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(422, 37, '2016-04-07 13:52:35', '2016-04-07 12:52:35', 'Much faster would be to do this:\n<pre>var handler = new FieldHandler(item, FieldRetriever); \nvar selected = handler.GetLov(field_code); \nif (selected != null &amp;&amp; selected.Code.Equals(value_code, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)) \n{ \n// Do something \n}</pre>', 'How to work with ComboBox custom fields?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '421-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-07 13:52:35', '2016-04-07 12:52:35', '', 421, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/421-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(423, 37, '2016-04-07 14:11:57', '2016-04-07 13:11:57', 'A filter can be created to retrieve specified fields from the item(s) you need.\n<pre>var filter = new ItemFilter\n{\n    // Visible fields of the items you need later\n    VisibleItemFields = new List\n    {\n        new ItemField { FieldId = FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(&quot;SF2&quot;) },\n        new ItemField { FieldId = FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(&quot;SF7&quot;) },\n        new ItemField { FieldId = FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(&quot;SF25&quot;) }\n    }.ToArray(),\n    // Criteria for fields of your filter\n    ItemFilterCriteria = new List\n    {\n        new ItemFilterCriterion { FieldId = FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(&quot;SF19&quot;), Value = ScriptContext.Indicator.List.Id.ToString() },\n        new ItemFilterCriterion { FieldId = FieldRetriever.GetFieldId(&quot;SF7&quot;), Value = &quot;AA&quot; } // &#039;Appears Active&#039; statuses\n    }.ToArray()\n};\n \nif (!Api.ItemFilters.GetItemsByItemFilter(filter))\n  throw new ScriptException(&quot;GetItemsByItemFilter - An error occurred: &quot; +Api.ItemFilters.ErrorMessage);\nreturn filter.Items;</pre>', 'How to filter items?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-07 14:11:57', '2016-04-07 13:11:57', '', 302, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
