ision', '', 0),
(426, 36, '2016-04-08 15:11:11', '2016-04-08 14:11:11', 'In a script it might be useful to redirect the user to a certain item, list, smart list or workspace. This can all be done, using the NavigationScriptResultType.\n<pre>// TODO: target to redirect to\nobject target = ... // Item, List or Workspace\n\n// Redirect using the &#039;Navigation&#039; ScriptResultType\nScriptContext.ResultType = ScriptResultType.Navigation;\nScriptContext.Result = Navigator.UrlFor(target);</pre>', 'How to redirect to a item after execution of a script?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '329-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-08 15:11:11', '2016-04-08 14:11:11', '', 329, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/329-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(427, 36, '2016-04-08 15:26:33', '2016-04-08 14:26:33', 'The same can be achieved with less code when the common add-in is used:\n<pre>var query = Pmx.Items(FieldRetriever)\n    .Where(SF.List, f =&gt; f.Equals(list))\n    .Where(SF.Nr, f =&gt; f.Equals(&quot;5515&quot;))\n    .Select(SF.Title, SF.Status);\nvar result = query.Execute();</pre>\nNote that there are various other kinds of matching, such as <em>StartsWith</em>, <em>Contains</em>, <em>EndsWith</em>, <em>NotEquals</em>, <em>Between</em>, :\n<pre>var query = Pmx.Items(FieldRetriever)\n    .Where(SF.List, f =&gt; f.Equals(listid))\n    .Where(SF.Nr, f =&gt; f.StartsWith(&quot;55&quot;))\n    .Where(SF.CreatedOn, f =&gt; f.Between(date1, date2))\n    .Select(SF.Title, SF.Nr);</pre>', 'How to use exact matching in an itemfilter', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-use-exact-matching-in-an-itemfilter', '', '', '2016-04-08 15:30:03', '2016-04-08 14:30:03', '', 424, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-to-use-exact-matching-in-an-itemfilter/?show_answer=427#answer_427', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
