(437, 14, '2016-04-13 11:07:11', '2016-04-13 10:07:11', 'This can only be solved at moments the system is not in use.\n\nYou need access to the web application server in order to do these steps. Please contact your server administrator for assistance.\n\nTo do this the following setting needs to be adjusted in the appsettings.config file\n<pre>    &lt;!--timeout used for file uploading--&gt;\n    &lt;add key=&quot;timeout&quot; value=&quot;6000&quot; /&gt;</pre>\nThe timeout is specified in seconds, so setting it to 6000 gives you 100 minutes time to run the import.\n\nAfter this the web application needs to be restarted and the import can be run again.', 'Which timeout parameter should I change to avoid my thread is being aborted?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'which-timeout-parameter-should-i-change-to-avoid-my-thread-is-being-aborted', '', '', '2016-04-13 11:07:11', '2016-04-13 10:07:11', '', 436, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/which-timeout-parameter-should-i-change-to-avoid-my-thread-is-being-aborted/?show_answer=437#answer_437', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
