(482, 8, '2016-04-25 13:08:09', '2016-04-25 12:08:09', 'Use the SetActionButtonHidden method of the FieldHandler class\n<pre>// Updated / Created item\nvar item = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter(NewItem) as Item;\n// Make a FieldHandler for the item\nvar fh = new FieldHandler(item);\n\n// Load the ListScripts on the List property of the FieldHandler \nApi.ListScripts.GetListScriptsByList(itemfh.List);\n// Find the id of the button by Caption\nint listScriptId = itemfh.List.ListScripts.FirstOrDefault(s =&gt; s.ButtonCaption == &quot;Caption of the button&quot;).Id;\n\n// Hide the button\nfh.SetActionButtonHidden(listScriptId, true);</pre>', 'How can I show/hide specific buttons in a buttonstrip via scripting', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-can-i-showhide-specific-buttons-in-a-buttonstrip-via-scripting', '', '', '2016-04-26 08:47:34', '2016-04-26 07:47:34', '', 481, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-can-i-showhide-specific-buttons-in-a-buttonstrip-via-scripting/?show_answer=482#answer_482', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
