(503, 14, '2016-04-25 15:36:29', '2016-04-25 14:36:29', 'This feature is only recommended for acceptance environments when looking at the performance.\n\nThis can only be solved at moments the system is not in use.\n\nYou need access to the web application server in order to do these steps. Please contact your server administrator for assistance.\n\nTo do this the following parameter needs to be set to \'1\':\n\n<!-- Crayon Syntax Highlighter v_2.7.2_beta -->\n\nShowTitleBarTimings = 293\n\nThis can be done with a one time formula or an odata call\nAfter the parameter has been set the web application has to be restarted', 'How can I make response times of the service calls/db calls visible in the browser tabs?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-can-i-make-response-times-of-the-service-callsdb-calls-visible-in-the-browser-tabs', '', '', '2016-04-25 15:36:29', '2016-04-25 14:36:29', '', 485, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/questions/question/how-can-i-make-response-times-of-the-service-callsdb-calls-visible-in-the-browser-tabs/?show_answer=503#answer_503', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(504, 8, '2016-04-26 08:47:34', '2016-04-26 07:47:34', 'Use the SetActionButtonHidden method of the FieldHandler class\n<pre>// Updated / Created item\nvar item = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter(NewItem) as Item;\n// Make a FieldHandler for the item\nvar fh = new FieldHandler(item);\n\n// Load the ListScripts on the List property of the FieldHandler \nApi.ListScripts.GetListScriptsByList(itemfh.List);\n// Find the id of the button by Caption\nint listScriptId = itemfh.List.ListScripts.FirstOrDefault(s =&gt; s.ButtonCaption == &quot;Caption of the button&quot;).Id;\n\n// Hide the button\nfh.SetActionButtonHidden(listScriptId, true);</pre>', 'How can I show/hide specific buttons in a buttonstrip via scripting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '482-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-26 08:47:34', '2016-04-26 07:47:34', '', 482, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/482-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(505, 42, '2016-04-26 08:58:30', '2016-04-26 07:58:30', 'It is possible to use external assemblies in your script. In Visual Studio you can just add the assembly as reference, but we also have to load the assembly in pmOperation. First you have to store your assembly in the datahomefolder\\libraries. You can find your datahomefolder by going to Settings -&gt; Setup &amp; Configuration -&gt; Parameters and navigating to the File Upload tab.\n\nIn this example we have to store the assembly in c:\\tenforce\\nameprd\\libraries on the application server.\n\nNow we have to add a Reference region in the beginning of our script to load the assembly.\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp" data-enlighter-theme="classic">#region References\n/*\n/libpath\nRenci.SshNet.dll\n*/\n#endregion</pre>\nIn this example the /libpath means datahomefolder\\libraries, and from there we load the Renci.SshNet.dll assembly.\n\nYou can also load assemblies from other paths.\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp" data-enlighter-theme="classic">#regionReferences\n/*\n/libpath\nRenci.SshNet.dll\n*/\n#endregion</pre>\n&nbsp;\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp" data-enlighter-theme="classic">#region References\n/*\n/libpath C:\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\nSystem.DirectoryServices.dll\nSystem.DirectoryServices.AccountManagement.dll\n*/\n#endregion</pre>\nIn this example we load the System.DirectoryServices.* assemblies from the path C:\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319.\n\nYou can also combine multiple paths.\n<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="csharp" data-enlighter-theme="classic">#region References\n/*\n/libpath\nRenci.SshNet.dll\n/libpath C:\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\nSystem.DirectoryServices.dll\nSystem.DirectoryServices.AccountManagement.dll\n*/\n#endregion</pre>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Reference external assemblies', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '203-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-26 08:58:30', '2016-04-26 07:58:30', '', 203, 'http://devcenter.tenforce.com/portal/203-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
