(92, 1, '2016-02-04 10:19:35', '2016-02-04 09:19:35', '<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>\r\nScripting in pmOperation is done in C#. Therefore all development is done in Visual Studio.\r\n<h1 id="setting-up-development-environment">Setting up development environment</h1>\r\n<h2 id="visual-studio-2013">Visual Studio 2013</h2>\r\n<h3 id="installing-templates">Installing TenForce templates</h3>\r\nI have setup a private extension gallery for visual studio 2012. This way we can auto update our TenForce Addin templates inside Visual Studio.\r\nHere are the steps to configure it :\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open Microsoft Visual Studio and go to \'Tools\' &gt; \'Extensions and Updates\'</li>\r\n	<li>Addthe TenforceGallery.reg(you can find it <a href="http://dev.tenforce.eu/tenforcegallery/tenforcegallery.reg" target="_blank">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Inthe \'Online\' tab forthe \'TenForceGallery\', press the \'Download\' button to installthe \'TenForce API2 Templates\'</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Capture_1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-260"><img class="alignnone wp-image-260" src="http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Capture_1-300x207.png" alt="Capture_1" width="468" height="323" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id="creating-an-add-in-project">Creating an add-in project</h2>\r\nFrom the Visual Studio menu select File -&gt; New project and select TenForce Addin (Api2).\r\n\r\n<img class="" src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-4.png" alt="" width="467" height="362" />\r\n\r\nPress \'OK\'. The add-in settings screen will popup.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-5.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Site ID</dt><dd>Put 0 in here.\r\n<strong>Addin ID\r\n</strong>Unique ID for your add-in.</dd></dl>Press \'Ok\' to create the add-in solution.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAfter creation of the project, set the Emulator project as startup project\r\n\r\n<img src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-6.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 id="copy-application-assemblies">Copy application assemblies</h2>\r\nWe need the pmOperation assemblies because these are referenced in the add-in project. These assemblies contain the Api2 methods used in scripting. It is important to use the correct version of the assemblies. The version you use in your add-in project should be the same as the pmOperation version you use. You can find the pmOperation version on the bottom left when navigating to http(s)://&lt;pmoperation url&gt;/config.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-7.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nTo find out the assemblies version, right click on the assembly, select properties and navigate to the details tab.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-8.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nIn this example the 2.183.915.0 stands for\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 = Major version</li>\r\n	<li>183 = Minor version</li>\r\n	<li>915 = Database version</li>\r\n	<li>0 = Patch version</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnder the directory &lt;add-in name&gt;\\&lt;add-in name&gt;, create a directory called dlls.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://dev.tenforce.com/img/dev-tut/set-up-9.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nCopy all .dll files from the pmOperation \\bin folder to the dlls folder.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'TenForce development walkthrough - Visual Studio', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tenforce-development-walkthrough-visualstudio', '', '', '2016-04-26 09:03:30', '2016-04-26 08:03:30', '', 0, 'http://www.tenforce.com/portal/?post_type=tutorials&#038;p=92', 0, 'tutorials', '', 0) ;
