(255, 6, '2016-02-16 14:22:07', '2016-02-16 13:22:07', 'Here is an example on retrievingthe list of values of a combobox custom field\n<pre>// TODO: provide custom field code\nvar field_code = &quot;...&quot;;\n// Get custom field definition\nvar field = FieldRetriever.GetCustomField(field_code);\n// Get list of values for the custom combo box field\nif (!Api.CustomFieldDefinitionListsOfValues.GetCustomFieldDefinitionListOfValuesByCustomFieldDefinition(field))\n  throw new ScriptException(&quot;Could not retrieve list of values&quot;);\nvar values = field.CustomFieldDefinitionListOfValues;</pre>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you want to compare the value of a combobox with a selected value, you can use this code:\n<pre>// TODO: provide custom field code and value code\nvar field_code = &quot;...&quot;;\nvar value_code = &quot;...&quot;;\n// Get custom field definition\nvar field = FieldRetriever.GetCustomField(field_code);\n// Get list of values for the custom combo box field\nif (!Api.CustomFieldDefinitionListsOfValues.GetCustomFieldDefinitionListOfValuesByCustomFieldDefinition(field))\n  throw new ScriptException(&quot;Could not retrieve list of values&quot;);\n\n// Find value with the given value code\nvar value = field\n  .CustomFieldDefinitionListOfValues\n  .Where(v =&gt; v.Code.Equals(value_code, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))\n  .FirstOrDefault();\nif (value == null)\n  throw new ScriptException(&quot;Could not find value&quot;);\n// Get value identifier\nvar id = value.Id;\n\n// Compare with selected value\nvar handler = new FieldHandler(item, FieldRetriever);\nvar selected = handler.GetInt(field_code);\nif (selected == id)\n{\n  ...\n}</pre>', 'How to work with ComboBox custom fields?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-work-with-combobox-custom-fields', '', '', '2016-02-16 14:22:41', '2016-02-16 13:22:41', '', 253, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-to-work-with-combobox-custom-fields/?show_answer=255#answer_255', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
