(295, 6, '2016-02-23 09:07:58', '2016-02-23 08:07:58', 'To create a new item in a certain list and set AssignedTo:\n<pre>var item = ScriptContext.ScriptParameters.GetParameter(&quot;Item&quot;) as Item;\nif (item == null) return;\n\n//TODO - Get correct &#039;Attendances&#039; list\nvar listId = ...;\n//Create a new item and link it to the current item\nvar ih = new ItemsHandler(FieldRetriever);\nvar newChildItem = new FieldHandler(ih.CreateItemResource(new List { Id = listId }, null), FieldRetriever);\nnewChildItem.SetInt(&quot;SF4&quot;, ScriptContext.CurrentUserContextPersonId);\n//Link\nnewChildItem.Item.Parent = item;\nif (!Api.Items.Create(newChildItem.Item, true)) \n    throw new ScriptException(&quot;An error occurred while creating a (child) &#039;Start Attendance&#039; item: &quot; + Api.Items.ErrorMessage);</pre>', 'How to create a new item in a certain list as child item of an existing item?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-create-a-new-item-in-a-certain-list-as-child-item-of-an-existing-item', '', '', '2016-02-23 09:08:15', '2016-02-23 08:08:15', '', 288, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-to-create-a-new-item-in-a-certain-list-as-child-item-of-an-existing-item/?show_answer=295#answer_295', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
