(405, 11, '2016-04-04 15:43:16', '2016-04-04 14:43:16', '<h1><a name="_Toc447550911"></a>Introduction</h1>\r\nTenForce provides a solution to import items in bulk using an Excel file. We allow the bulk import user to import all items of an Excel file into one specific workspace.\r\n\r\nWhile importing data into the TenForce application, the bulk import user must provide the prepared Excel <u>file</u> and the <u>workspace</u>.\r\n<h1><a name="_Toc447550912"></a>Content Excel file</h1>\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550913"></a>Worksheets</h2>\r\n<h3>Mapping the list</h3>\r\nAn Excel file contains a number of worksheets. The name of the worksheet must match the list code in the given workspace. All records in the worksheet will be imported in that list.\r\n\r\nThe import is skipped for items in a worksheet of which the name doesnt match any list in the given workspace.\r\n\r\nThe sequence of the worksheets is not relevant. If a sequence between lists is relevant, then different excel imports are required.\r\n<h4>FAQ: How to retrieve the list code</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Settings</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>Expand the topic <strong>Workspaces and their setup</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Workspaces</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>workspace name</strong> to open the detail screen</li>\r\n	<li>Open the <strong>Lists</strong> tab</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the <strong>list name</strong> to open the list settings page</li>\r\n	<li>The code of the lists is visualized in the field: <strong>Code</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h5>Prerequisite</h5>\r\nIn order to view workspaces, view workspace application privileges must be granted to you. The workspace access rights to view workspace settings need to be assigned to you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550914"></a>Records</h2>\r\n<h3>Containing the items</h3>\r\nEach row in the workspace will represent a new item in the TenForce application. To map each field, a header must be foreseen in the first record. The header contains the represented field code. A field code is unique in the TenForce application.\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550915"></a>Record reference</h3>\r\nOne of the TenForce application strengths is the hierarchical structure between items. TenForce allows you to import that hierarchical structure in one import.\r\n\r\nTo obtain this feature, each worksheet <strong>must start</strong> with 2 fixed columns:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ExcelId &gt; The first column in every worksheet</li>\r\n	<li>ParentExcelId &gt;The second column in every worksheet</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll other fields will be added into next following columns (see: Field mapping)\r\n<blockquote>Hint: During the import, an ExcelId has no mapping with the TenForce application ItemId.</blockquote>\r\n<h4>ExcelId</h4>\r\nThe ExcelId is a unique identifier of the record within the entire Excel file.\r\n<h4>ParentExcelId</h4>\r\nThe Parent ExcelId will contain an ExcelId. During the import of the items, the parent item is retrieved by its ParentExcelId.\r\n<blockquote>Hint: Note that both the parent and child item are part of the Excel file and thus both records are created as new items.</blockquote>\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550916"></a>Field mapping</h3>\r\nThe column order will not have any affect during the import.\r\n\r\nA standard field is a product defined field and needed by the TenForce application to ensure the correct working of it. The FieldId is fixed for standard fields. It representation can be like SF followed by a number, or a text. The FieldId or code can be found at:\r\n<a href="http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/tutorials/standard-fields-and-their-ids-sf/">http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/tutorials/standard-fields-and-their-ids-sf/</a>\r\n<blockquote>Hint: TenForce prefers to use the FieldId of the standard field.</blockquote>\r\nCustom fields are customer specific fields needed to enhance the customer configurations needs. The FieldId is represented as CF followed by a number, or using the code of the custom field.\r\n<blockquote>Hint: TenForce prefers to use the code of the custom field.</blockquote>\r\n<h4>FAQ: How to retrieve the field code of a custom field</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Settings</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>Expand the topic <strong>Workspaces and their setup</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Custom fields</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>The code of the field is visualized in the field: <strong>Code</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h5>Prerequisite</h5>\r\nIn order to view custom fields, view custom fields application privileges must be granted to you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550917"></a>Field values</h3>\r\nTo be able to import items, all required fields, both standard and custom fields, must contain a valid value during the import. The content of all other fields are optional. The value given for each field must be valid for that particular item, otherwise validation exceptions are thrown and will cause the import to fail.\r\n\r\nUse a semicolon ( ; ) or comma ( , ) separated lists to import multiple values into one field. This is only possible for fields supporting multi selections.\r\n\r\nDepending on the fields type, different conversions may occur.\r\nThe following objects are retrieved in following order:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Users\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>By: email</li>\r\n	<li>By: firstname lastname</li>\r\n	<li>By: lastname firstname</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>ItemStatuses\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>By: screenlabel</li>\r\n	<li>By: code</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Dropdowns (include multi selection)\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>By: sequence</li>\r\n	<li>By: code</li>\r\n	<li>By: screenlabel</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Items (include multi selection)\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>By: title of the item</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote>Hint: If the value is not found, then this excel value is skipped.</blockquote>\r\nCulture conversions are based on the running users culture settings. The conversion may effect following field types:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Date</li>\r\n	<li>Time</li>\r\n	<li>Date and time</li>\r\n	<li>Number</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550918"></a>Visualized</h2>\r\n<a href="http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_04042016_151231.png" rel="attachment wp-att-406"><img class="alignnone wp-image-406" src="http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_04042016_151231-300x145.png" alt="Import items" width="906" height="438" /></a>\r\n\r\nFigure 1: Excel file layout example\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><a name="_Toc447550919"></a>Importing items</h1>\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550920"></a>Executing the import</h2>\r\nThe user who will be responsible to import the data is able to start the bulk import using the Administration Script: Import Items.\r\n\r\nFollowing parameters are asked:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>File The excel file containing the items</li>\r\n	<li>Workspace The workspace used for importing the data</li>\r\n	<li>Include hierarchy Optional parameter, set active if the flag is available</li>\r\n	<li>Template items Optional parameter</li>\r\n	<li>Trigger events Optional parameter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550921"></a>Include hierarchy</h3>\r\nThe include hierarchy flag is not always available. When it is available, you should activate it in order to successfully import the data with hierarchy. Documentation is available on how to import items without hierarchy.\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550922"></a>Template items</h3>\r\nItems can be created as templates. Templates are used in the application to create new items based on an item preset.\r\n\r\nNote: Template items can only be configured by workspace administrators\r\n<h3><a name="_Toc447550923"></a>Trigger events</h3>\r\nDuring creation of the items, automation scripts can be triggered. Trigger events will have a performance impact but in some cases it is necessary. TenForce promotes not to enable this flag during import of items.\r\n<h4>FAQ: How to execute an administration script</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Settings</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>Expand the topic <strong>Setup &amp; configuration</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Administration Scripts</strong> link</li>\r\n	<li>Click the <strong>Import items</strong> to open the detail screen</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the <strong>Execute</strong> action</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h5>Prerequisite</h5>\r\nIn order to execute administration scripts, view administration scripts and execute administration scripts application privileges must be granted to you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550924"></a>How it works</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>All active lists are retrieved from the given workspace</li>\r\n	<li>The Excel file is opened for reading</li>\r\n	<li>Every worksheet is retrieved and mapped to the active lists\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Worksheets not mapped with a list are skipped</li>\r\n	<li>The header is translated for field mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Non existing fields are skipped</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Every record is retrieved and imported\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The item is created based on the worksheets list</li>\r\n	<li>The ExcelId is kept as reference for the newly created item</li>\r\n	<li>Values are converted to match:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Culture settings (example: dates)</li>\r\n	<li>Application identifiers (example: dropdowns)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Values are added into a new item</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>For every field where the ParentExcelId is defined, the mapped item is linked as parent item</li>\r\n	<li>A bulk insert occurs for all items in the Excel file</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<blockquote>Hint: Automations, mapped to the lists, are <strong>not</strong> triggered during creation of the items.</blockquote>\r\n<h2><a name="_Toc447550925"></a>Exceptions</h2>\r\nWhen an exception occurs, the entire import will be roll backed. This means nothing is saved in the application.\r\n\r\nExceptions are thrown when\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Incorrect file format\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Make only use of an Excel file with the format: .xslx</li>\r\n	<li>User has no creation privileges\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Make sure you have sufficient privileges or ask a workspace administrator</li>\r\n	<li>Mandatory fields arent defined\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Add the mandatory fields as columns to your Excel file for the given lists</li>\r\n	<li>Mandatory field values are not set\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Add valid values into the cells of the required fields</li>\r\n	<li>Trigger events throws an exception\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Add valid values into the cells\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Disable the flag, ask the workspace administrator for the impact</li>\r\n	<li>Invalid date ranges\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Provide a correct date format defined in your user culture settings</li>\r\n	<li>Not all fields are imported\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Dont have empty columns within your selection</li>\r\n	<li>Not all items are created\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Dont have empty rows within your selection</li>\r\n	<li>Parent-child relation is not created\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Make sure the Include hierarchical flag is active\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Validate the ParentExcelId is mapping to the correct ExcelId</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Import items with hierarchy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'import-items-with-hierarchy', '', '', '2016-04-26 08:26:39', '2016-04-26 07:26:39', '', 0, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/?post_type=tutorials&#038;p=405', 0, 'tutorials', '', 0),
