(418, 25, '2016-04-07 10:17:00', '2016-04-07 09:17:00', 'Nice to know: Before version 2.220 the product code contained a "lock" when executing admin scripts. This means that when you execute a script while another one is running, this script will only start when the first one ends.', 'How to trigger an admin script via OData from within INCA?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-trigger-an-admin-script-via-odata-from-within-inca', '', '', '2016-04-07 10:17:00', '2016-04-07 09:17:00', '', 134, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-to-trigger-an-admin-script-via-odata-from-within-inca/?show_answer=418#answer_418', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(419, 25, '2016-04-07 10:33:15', '2016-04-07 09:33:15', 'In the example above, setting the Int, Number and Boolean value should be:\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetInt</span><span>(</span><span>int_field_code</span><span>,</span> <span>3</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetNumber</span><span>(</span><span>int_field_code</span><span>,3M</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n<span>handler</span><span>.</span><span>SetBool</span><span>(</span><span>bool_field_code</span><span>,</span> <span>true</span><span>)</span><span>;</span>\n\nsettingmultiple int :\nhandler.SetMultipleInts("mulpiple_field_code", new List&lt;int&gt;() { 1, 2, 3 });\nhandler.SetMultipleIntsByCodes("mulpiple_field_code", new List&lt;int&gt;() { "lov_code_1", "lov_code_2", "lov_code_3" });', 'How to retrieve and update multiple fields of an item?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item-2', '', '', '2016-04-07 10:33:15', '2016-04-07 09:33:15', '', 318, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-to-retrieve-and-update-multiple-fields-of-an-item/?show_answer=419#answer_419', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
