(444, 21, '2016-04-18 15:50:17', '2016-04-18 14:50:17', 'Is there a script I can use to export all custom fields to an excel file?', 'Is there a script I can use to export all custom fields to an excel file?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'is-there-a-script-i-can-use-to-export-all-custom-fields-to-an-excel-file', '', '', '2016-04-18 15:50:17', '2016-04-18 14:50:17', '', 0, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/is-there-a-script-i-can-use-to-export-all-custom-fields-to-an-excel-file/', 0, 'question', '', 0),
(445, 36, '2016-04-18 15:57:30', '2016-04-18 14:57:30', 'The common add-in contains a library script for exporting custom fields and LOVs: Pmx.Export.CustomFields\n\nHeres a one-time script that downloads an Excel file containing all custom fields and LOVs:\n<pre>using TenForce.Execution.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2.Objects;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.AddIns.Common;\n\nnamespace TenForce.OneTime\n{\n    public class ExportCustomFields : Script&lt;ScriptContext&gt;\n    {\n        &#91;EntryPoint&#93;\n        public void RunCode()\n        {\n            // Export custom fields and LOVs to file\n            var path = Pmx.Export.CustomFields(true);\n            // Download file\n            ScriptContext.ResultType = ScriptResultType.FileLocation;\n            ScriptContext.Result = path;                        \n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\nSimply add a workspace parameter to Pmx.Export.CustomFields to limit the fields to that given workspace', 'Is there a script I can use to export all custom fields to an excel file?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'is-there-a-script-i-can-use-to-export-all-custom-fields-to-an-excel-file', '', '', '2016-04-18 16:05:01', '2016-04-18 15:05:01', '', 444, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/is-there-a-script-i-can-use-to-export-all-custom-fields-to-an-excel-file/?show_answer=445#answer_445', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(446, 36, '2016-04-18 16:05:01', '2016-04-18 15:05:01', 'The common add-in contains a library script for exporting custom fields and LOVs: Pmx.Export.CustomFields\n\nHeres a one-time script that downloads an Excel file containing all custom fields and LOVs:\n<pre>using TenForce.Execution.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Api2.Objects;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting;\nusing TenForce.Execution.Scripting.Api2;\nusing TenForce.Execution.AddIns.Common;\n\nnamespace TenForce.OneTime\n{\n    public class ExportCustomFields : Script&lt;ScriptContext&gt;\n    {\n        &#91;EntryPoint&#93;\n        public void RunCode()\n        {\n            // Export custom fields and LOVs to file\n            var path = Pmx.Export.CustomFields(true);\n            // Download file\n            ScriptContext.ResultType = ScriptResultType.FileLocation;\n            ScriptContext.Result = path;                        \n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\nSimply add a workspace parameter to Pmx.Export.CustomFields to limit the fields to that given workspace', 'Is there a script I can use to export all custom fields to an excel file?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '445-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-18 16:05:01', '2016-04-18 15:05:01', '', 445, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/445-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
