(574, 20, '2016-05-13 11:00:41', '2016-05-13 10:00:41', '<ol>\n	<li>Create a folder in your project and name it Files</li>\n	<li>Create resource files for the languages you want to support</li>\n	<li>Reference the common library</li>\n	<li>Create a Translations class who derives frol TranslationsImpl&lt;Translations&gt;. This class should be of type LibraryFunction in the application. 112 is the addin number.</li>\n</ol>\n<pre>#region AddInReferences\n/*\n112\\Files\\StringsEn.resx\n112\\Files\\StringsNl.resx\n112\\Files\\StringsFr.resx\n112\\Files\\StringsDe.resx\n*/\n#endregion\n\npublic class Translations : TranslationsImpl&lt;Translations&gt;\n{\n        public static string RemarkDefinition { get { return Get(&quot;RemarkDefinition&quot;); } }\n}</pre>\n5. Reference the resource files in your Translations class\n\n5. You can use the Get method to make your strings strongly typed as the example above.\n\n6. If you want to throw an exception, you can do it as follows:\n<pre>throw new ScriptException(Translations.RemarkDefinition);</pre>\n7. The resource files will be installed on the server through an add-in. Do not forget to install an add-in when you update the resource files.\n\n8. If there is no definition in the resource file, the Get method will return the string between brackets.', 'How can i make my scripts multilingual (errormessages, feedback&#8230;)?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-can-i-make-my-scripts-multilingual-errormessages-feedback', '', '', '2016-05-13 11:00:41', '2016-05-13 10:00:41', '', 566, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-can-i-make-my-scripts-multilingual-errormessages-feedback/?show_answer=574#answer_574', 0, 'answer', '', 0),
(575, 3, '2016-05-15 20:08:19', '2016-05-15 19:08:19', 'I want toaccess raw data of Tracker (like one of my Smartlists).\r\nI want for example to be able to retrieve our current sprint backlog,without actually going to Tracker.\r\n\r\nI want to consume the info in my app.\r\n\r\nHow can this be done ?\r\n\r\nThanks!', 'How do I consume Tracker info using OData?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-consume-tracker-info-using-odata', '', '', '2016-05-15 20:08:19', '2016-05-15 19:08:19', '', 0, 'http://tenforce.konstantinkharlov.com/questions/question/how-do-i-consume-tracker-info-using-odata/', 0, 'question', '', 0),
